rComments: Def. the worst prof I have ever had! Made frequent mistakes during lectures, misapplied concepts in midterm questions. Her own solutions to problem sets were incorrect yet she refused to discuss or admit to her mistakes, and instead penalized students if they didn't agree with her. Was absolutely no help outside of class. Avoid at all cost

Shelley doesn't really prepare students to succeed. She established a "problem based" course, yet never assigned any HW problems or even a textbook. Past tests were not provided no was the format of the test. Half the people dropped after the midterm and she practically ruined a course. But at the end of the day, I did learn a lot from her teaching

Worst professor I've had at UofT. Unwilling to admit mistakes or hold office hours. I hope she never gets another job teaching and just stays in the lab. Leave teaching to those who actually care about their students and can actually do a good job.

THE worst prof i have ever had at uoft. DO NOT take any courses with her. I had to take her course for a prereq. After the midterm, half the class dropped. The class average for the first midterm was 48% and the assignment are very unclear. Terrible.
